# File Versioning Details

## Archive Process

1. Check if `zArchive/` exists in parent directory; create if not
2. Use terminal to check existing versions for today (cursorignore blocks normal access)
3. Copy to `zArchive/YY-MM-DD V[n] - original name`
4. Tell user what was archived, then proceed

**Version numbering:** Resets each day. If V1 exists today, use V2.

## Terminal Commands

Google Drive paths require `required_permissions: ["all"]`

```bash
ls -la "path/to/zArchive/"                              # List archives
cat "path/to/zArchive/YY-MM-DD V1 - file.md"            # Read archived file
cp "path/to/file.md" "path/to/zArchive/YY-MM-DD V1 - file.md"       # Archive file
cp -r "path/to/dir" "path/to/zArchive/YY-MM-DD V1 - dir"            # Archive directory
```

## Review and Restore

**Review:** List zArchive contents, present options, show requested version.

**Restore:** Archive current version first (safety net), then apply archived content.

## Example

```
project/
├── Strategy.md
└── zArchive/
    ├── 26-01-08 V1 - Strategy.md
    ├── 26-01-10 V1 - Strategy.md
    └── 26-01-10 V2 - Strategy.md   # Second archive same day
```
